The injured to a serious accident a car is out of the hospital but rather of time apres it has of return in view of the infection MRSA and, since, the doctors could not make him a major operation has cause of the bacteria which is in his body.
Jusqu'au 10 december of this year, 1 094 infections hospitalieres generated by a agent pathogene multirésistant have been declared in Systeme national of surveillance nosocomiale, said Karolina Böröcz, a doctor in the head of the center national of the epidemiology.
In short it is the number of infections caused by an agent pathogene multirésistant that has actually been made in the hospitals and for the rest we do not have any information.
Environ two thirds of infections In particular 683 infections) have been caused by the MRSA, that is to say by the staphylococcus aureus resistance has the méthicilline-oxacilline.
A third of people are carriers of the bacteria of Staphylococcus aureus In particular S. A.) in their nose when it is a disease.
These infections caused by them S. A. In particular those that angines, amygdalites, infections skin, infections traumatic) responding well to antibiotics, they are easily guérissables.
Cependant, if the antibiotics are used of maniere excessive or inappropriate, the bacteria, which responds well to antibiotics, develop a bacterium very resistant to antibiotics which proliférera quickly in the poor conditions hospitalieres.
When the poor functioning temporary or extended of systeme the immune system, that bacteria can cause infections hospitalieres serious, as that a traumatic infection or a septicémie, on the older patients, of small weight or have a body weakened.
Selon the head doctor of the hospital János, it is nothing of particular in the number MRSA, these infections are part of everyday life of hospitals.
It must certainly not confuse the infection with the disease, we do not is not of MRSA only the or we do the is not, said Tibor Nyulasi.
They S. A. resistance to antibiotics.
" People who suffer from these diseases are isolated, the staff care is of punches in rubber and of masks of protection and we have antibiotics used to treat them ", said Tibor Nyulasi.
First and foremost, the hospital patients are considered they are carriers of MRSA, however the infection can not always be avoided.
The prélevement of the sample is not has the way
The vast majority of infections caused by the MRSA could be prevented but the conditions and the current circumstances are not right, in the hungarian hospitals, to prevent the development and the proliferation of agents pathogenes multirésistants, says Karolina Böröcz.
Of course it takes place mainly in the hospitals and in the houses for people older, the hospitals should control the hospital patients and isolate immediately the sick carriers of MRSA.
Toutefois the prélevement microbiological not is not has the way in the hungarian hospitals.
It must know that the body national of security social being financed not these tests.
Most cases do not see the day that if the infection MRSA is detectable on the patient, said the doctor in charge of the center epidemiological.
The European Union has recommendations strict relating has the appropriate use of antibiotics in medicine human and it is of directives hungary also for the recovery of some infections and syndrome.
We must make an effort so that the antibiotic therapy be targeted, other words tests microbiological should be made to of empecher the resistance to the drugs but the hospitals there are not always account.
The implementation of prélevements microbiological is even more rare in the care ambulatoires and in the care of the basis, has said Karolina Böröcz.
Many hospitals are the economy on the mats
Evidence scientific evidence that the MRSA proliferent of a patient has a other the most often by the middle of staff medical.
It is therefore important of be washing their hands, of put of gloves and of truth of protection. Toutefois shortcomings important are detected in the hospitals also in this area.
They MRSA proliferent by infection transmitted through inhalation of someone and by the Member States. Cependant, in view of conditions in the hungarian hospitals, the patient infected can not always be isolated.
