In the end, the failure.
The Serbs and the Albanians of Kosovo have completed wednesday morning in Baden, in Austria, a sixth and final session of talks without have been overcome their differences on the future status of the separatist province.
«Il is regrettable that the parties does not have not been able of reach to an agreement on the statut», said the european ombudsman Wolfgang Ischinger, at a press conference in Vienna.
Soulignant that the peace in the region was «en jeu», his american counterpart, Frank Wisner, has urged Belgrade and Pristina to respect their commitments to safeguard the peace and the dialogue beyond the end of the negotiations.
«On no provision not of violence in the short term but we are getting in a period very difficile», has -t he added, which that of «tensions obvious existent».
The end of the mediation the 10 December
The mediators of the troika, which includes the European Union, the United States and Russia, be make a last time monday in Serbia and in Kosovo.
The future of the province population to 90% of ethnic Albanians could become clearer lorsqu'Ischinger, Wisner and the Ombudsman russian Alexander Botsane-Khartchenko leave their report to the Security Council of the United Nations, here on 10 december.
The discussions of Baden, almost of Vienna, was the sixth and last session of negotiations that the troika has been charged of a new mediation by the United Nations, in August last.
The Americans and Europeans see that their mediation will finish the 10 December.
The Russians, who have already blocked in the Security Council the granting of the independence in Kosovo, who them on the continuation of negotiations beyond of this date deadline.
«La Russia was and remains committed in favor of a solution negotiated, a solution of compromis», said Botsane-Khartchenko.
Declaration of independence unilaterally?
After eight years of directors un of Kosovo, the West believe that the independence under the supervision of the EU is the only solution viable.
Pristina be said ready to declare it so unilateral if the Security Council does not decides not in its favour.
Belgrade insists on a greater autonomy.
«Malheureusement, no agreement has been trouvé», has said the president of the autonomous authority of Kosovo, Fatmir Sejdiu, in the hotel of Baden which be held since Monday these «négociations of the last chance».
Hashim Thaci, former commander of the rebel Kosovo and future Prime Minister of the province, has been part of its regret.
At the same time it has added that the terms of autonomy presented by Belgrade «appartenait to a past that has led to murder and to of déportations».
«Effet domino»
The serbian president Boris Tadic has said for his part that a compromise was still possible, which in reverse the majority albanians of Kosovo against the consequences of a unilateral proclamation of the independence of the province.
Belgrade said particularly fear a «effet domino» in a region still weakened by the war of independence of years sinceâ 1990.
«Pour Serbia, has -t he said, this does not mean not that a compromise is possible. »
Tuesday, the serbian delegation had insisted that any decision should only in the Security Council, where his ally russia has a right of veto.
«Le Parliament of Kosovo will the last mot»
«Seule a solution to the members of the Security Council is acceptable for the Serbie», said the Prime Minister serbian, Vojislav Kostunica.
«Ces negotiations have lasted two years.
They must come to an end as they are: in the Security Council. »
Aux journalists, Fatmir Sedjiu had said that «le Parliament of Kosovo has the last word on the statut», adding that any unilateral declaration of independence of the part of ethnic Albanians be would «en concertation» with the West.
