Now the market of the american housing is a critical stage, the predators are to the market us of credit cards.
These analysts of in Goldman Sachs believe that the losses related to credit cards could achieve â· 99 billion if the infection is spreading of mortgages to other forms of credit to the consumer.
Signs of tension are clearly visible.
It is of increases in the rates of pay and of insolvency, it that way the shares of stock not recoverable or that the are, most of 30 days after.
HSBC has announced last month that it has taken â· 1.4 billion in its funds to the consumer, in part because of the weakness of those of cards.
It is still too early to panic.
The costs and the insolvencies are still moderate.
Selon Moody, a fiscal agency, the rate of the insolvency of 3.89 cent of troixième quarter is lower of almost a point in relation to its historic average.
The deterioration of the rate is partly explained by factors technical.
A change of laws in 2005 the United States, concerning the personal bankruptcy has caused an abrupt fall of archives of bankruptcy, which in turn has led of heavy losses for credit cards, the number of files In particular and therefore of rates of insolvency) could increase even if the conditions of loans would worsen.
The industry will also of rates of payment fixed, which put in enhanced the amount of debt month that the consumer must deal.
And the confidence in the sureté of capital of credit cards is quite strong despite the paralysis of other aspects of the structured finance.
Dennis Moroney of TowerGroup, a society of research, has predicted that the volume of emissions for 2007 will 25% higher to last year.
The links direct infection between the crisis of mortgages and the market of credit cards are certainly, the consumers could opt to increase their debt now that the loans property fair have disappeared.
Let us the issuers of cards are more attention to the flow of cash rather to the value of assets, and therefore the fall of price of the property has not necessarily led a change in the credibility of borrowers.
They could even bring benefits to the issuers of securities of credit.
The premiums to consumers for the payment of mortgages fall if the property costs less than the value of the loan, therefore, the debt by credit card become a priority for repayer all.
They issuers of cards are capable of respond much more quickly that the mortgage and with most of flexibility to such a situation of crisis, because they can change the rate of interest or alter the limits of rédit.
That should in theory reduce the risk of having a rapid resumption of action.
« We does not will not wake us up one morning and review all loans. » said Gary Perlin, the director of Capital One.
The fact a disaster financial of market of credit cards is unlikely, it is of high risk of having a consistent reduction.
The fact the lower price of the property and a contraction in the market value lead the United States to the recession, the industry must certainly be given to a grim future.
