These are not not the coffers of Warhols.
Those which links the concepts Sweden and cash in wood, view to Ikea, but not to Andy Warhol.
Or if?
At present, of funds in timber production in Sweden form of shadow on the list of œuvres of Warhol.
A large part of 1980s ten Brillo-Boxs of " These Stockholm " catalogued there are of contrefaÇons.
After that the swedish newspaper " Expressen " has put into question a few months ago the authenticity of Brillo-Boxs of the year 1968 of Andy Warhol, the internal research of Moderna Museet of Stockholm result today to a result désenchanteur: the Six " Brillo-Boxes ", which the former director of the museum Pontus Hulten has done gift in 1995 in Moderna Museet, are copies. and that a large part of other hundreds of Brillo-Boxen of " These Stockholm ", who move on the international market of the art.
The history former is enchevêtrée, a confusing series of production artistic and curatoriques.
In 1964, Warhol created to New York its first " Brillo-Boxes ", of funds in wood painted, which is based on the design rouge-bleu-blanc cardboard boxes of soap in a powder keg " Brillo ".
One exhibition of his work in Moderna Museet was in 1968 that with the agreement of Warhol. of hundreds of funds Brillo made of cardboard, They do not were not In particular for reasons financial) of Warhol, but had been directly delivered of the factory of cartonnage Brillo.
It was not here to œuvres of art, but instead of their cars, of samples of exposure.
At the same time, Warhol had well given the authorisation in 1968 of do produce some funds in wood Brillo in Sweden, which do not were also not given in Moderna Museet.
Des witnesses of the time speak today of about 15 funds in wood which at the time be entered of law in the history of the art and auctions, in which Brillo-Boxes original of Andy Wahrol allowed, with the appelation " These Stockholm ".
Some of them have reached in the sales to the auction most of 100 000 dollars.
The problem now is that the legendary director of a museum Pontus Hultén has said, with good reason, later that about 100 funds in wood had been produced and presented in Sweden in 1968, that Warhol it would then cédées.
In fact, the 105 funds of Hultén have been produced to Malmo in 1990 only, for an exhibition to St-Pétersbourg.
At the time, Warhol was already death for three years.
